Defeat Judas

column1: Judas had long ago given up his struggle. As he ascended the Clock Tower, the Black Star rose once more.

column3: Defeat Trinity

column1: Even after her memories were mixed with another's, Trinity still tried to prevent the birth of the Chosen One. That was, of course, futile.

column3: Defeat Dahal

column1: Only in a virtual world is such a thing possible... To mix two beings' memories... Because of this, Dahal short-circuited.

column3: Learn the name of God

column1: Ideon's self was slowly destroyed through the process of never-ending reincarnation, leaving him even more vulnerable to Judas' manipulation.

Defeat Jack

column1: While Jack's faith is unwavering, being banished to the furthest corner of the world left him unable to even come close to the Chosen One.

column3: Defeat Carlos

column1: Carlos was fed up with the constant sacrifice of his self in each reincarnation. His solution? Kill and replace the Chosen One.

column3: Defeat Parker

column1: Parker, betrayed by Judas, retreated with no conscience to the dark corners of the metro.

column3: Defeat Thor

column1: Thor understood Judas' ultimate goal, and paid the ultimate price of splitting his self to serve Judas.

column3: Defeat Gorger

column1: Gorger was a simple resident of Ultimopolis that sacrificed himself to Judas without regret... or any other feelings.

column1: Trinity could not stop this cycle, nor can she ever stop the wheel of reincarnation from spinning.
